Variable.Name: PerformanceMeasures
Variable.Notes: This spreadsheet is a convenient method for storing the custom KPI values for time to get to different parts of the model

Variable.Name: ArrivalToScanRow
Variable.Notes: The row number of the Arrival to scan KPI in the performance measures spreadsheet

Variable.Name: ScanToTreatmentRow
Variable.Notes: The row number of the scan to treatment KPI in the performance measures spreadsheet

Variable.Name: OnsetToTreatmentRow
Variable.Notes: The row number of the scan to treatment KPI in the performance measures spreadsheet

Variable.Name: Row
Variable.Notes: Useful for looping rows

Variable.Name: Col
Variable.Notes: Useful for looping cols

Variable.Name: TimeUntilNextStrokeArrival
Variable.Notes: Used for scheduling arrivals. Inter-arrival time of stroke patient

Variable.Name: NextStrokeArrivalType
Variable.Notes: Used for scheduling arrivals. Identifies if the patient arrives by ambulance, GP referral or self presentation

Variable.Name: TimeOfNextStrokeArrival
Variable.Notes: Used for scheduling arrivals. The time of the next stroke arrival in minutes counted from 0

Variable.Name: PauseSimulation
Variable.Notes: Used when jumping to the next stroke arrival. If = 1 then simulation pauses.

Variable.Name: SpeedAfterFastForward
Variable.Notes: The simulation speed after fast forwarding to the next stroke.

Variable.Name: StrokeArrivals
Variable.Notes: INPUT: Contains a list of the patient arrival times
Variable.Cell: Arrival schedule for stroke patients in minutes from zero
Arrivals can be simulated using the arrival model or taken from a trace

Variable.Name: HistogramScanTime
Variable.Notes: Histogram of the arrival to scan times

Variable.Name: PatientTrace
Variable.Notes: Contains a trace of the patient through the simulation

Variable.Name: License
Variable.Notes: The license window in minutes

Variable.Name: HistogramOTT
Variable.Notes: Histogram of the onset to treatment times. I.e. OTT for thrombolysed patients

Variable.Name: ReplicationOutput
Variable.Notes: Stores the performance measures for each replication. Each row is an independent replication

Variable.Name: StrokeOTA
Variable.Notes: INPUT: Contains a list of patient OTA times by replication
Variable.Cell: OTA samples correspond to the arrival schedules in StrokeArrivalSheet
OTA times can be simulated using the arrival model or taken from a trace

Variable.Name: ReferralMatrix
Variable.Notes: Contains the probabilities of patient referal to SU at different points in the process

Variable.Name: HistogramOTD_Contra
Variable.Notes: Histogram for onset to treatment DECISION for patients with contra indications

Variable.Name: ValidationScenarios
Variable.Notes: This spreadsheet contains a number of alternative scenarios (changes in variables) and is useful for validation. The scenario can be selected fromt the 'Scenario Control' menu.

Variable.Name: ExternalParameters
Variable.Notes: INPUT: This contains the list files that are imported by the model
Variable.Cell: Auto import data on start trial
